thread.title: Women's 15 km biathlon postponed due to high winds

author: Philip O'Connor
title: Women's 15 km biathlon postponed due to high winds
text:
PYEONGCHANG, South Korea (Reuters) - The high winds buffeting Pyeongchang have caused plenty of headaches for organizers with a number of Alpine skiing races already postponed and the womenâ€™s 15km individual biathlon became the latest to fall victim to bad weather on Wednesday.
German Laura Dahlmeier will be aiming to take her personal haul of gold medals in Pyeongchang to three when the event gets underway a day later than scheduled after it was put back until 5:15 p.m. (0815 GMT) on Thursday.
Reporting by Philip O'Connor; Editing by John O'Brien
